ing method Error)"},{"range":{"start":{"line":581,"character":42},"end":{"line":581,"character":44}},"severity":1,"code":"InvalidIfaceAssign","codeDescription":{"href":"https://pkg.go.dev/golang.org/x/tools/internal/typesinternal#InvalidIfaceAssign"},"source":"compiler","message":"cannot use wm (variable of type *mockServerWorkloadManager) as WorkloadManager value in argument to NewServer: *mockServerWorkloadManager does not implement WorkloadManager (missing method DeleteSandbox)"}],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/pkg/client/informers/externalversions/runtime/v1alpha1/interface.go":[{"range":{"start":{"line":3,"character":1},"end":{"line":3,"character":9}},"severity":1,"code":"UnusedImport","codeDescription":{"href":"https://pkg.go.dev/golang.org/x/tools/internal/typesinternal#UnusedImport"},"source":"compiler","message":"\"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1\" imported and not used","tags":[1]}],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/pkg/router/config.go":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/pkg/router/backend.go":[{"range":{"start":{"line":167,"character":2},"end":{"line":167,"character":11}},"severity":4,"code":"default","codeDescription":{"href":"https://pkg.go.dev/golang.org/x/tools/go/analysis/passes/modernize#mapsloop"},"source":"mapsloop","message":"Replace m[k]=v loop with maps.Copy"}]},"diff":"Index: /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-010/delta-spec.md\n===================================================================\n--- /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-010/delta-spec.md\n+++ /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-010/delta-spec.md\n@@ -14,37 +14,258 @@\n ---\n \n ## Background\n \n-The router module requires session management to maintain stateful connections and track client sessions to backend services.\n+The router module requires session management to maintain stateful connections and track client sessions to backend services. This enables sticky sessions, session affinity, lifecycle management, and operational visibility into active sessions.\n \n ---\n \n-## Requirement: Session Storage\n+## Requirement: Session Configuration\n \n-### Scenario: Router creates session for new client\n+### Scenario: Router creates session store with default configuration\n \n+**GIVEN** a Router instance is created with `sessionEnabled: true` and no explicit session configuration\n+**WHEN** the router initializes\n+**THEN** it SHOULD use default values: session timeout `30m`, cookie name `\"AGENTSESSIONID\"`, max active sessions `10000`, cleanup interval `5m`\n+\n+### Scenario: Router creates session store with custom configuration\n+\n+**GIVEN** a Router instance is created with session configuration: `sessionTimeout: \"60m\"`, `sessionCookieName: \"SID\"`, `sessionMaxActive: 5000`\n+**WHEN** the router initializes\n+**THEN** it SHOULD configure session timeout to 60 minutes, cookie name to \"SID\", and limit to 5000 concurrent sessions\n+\n+### Scenario: Router disables session management\n+\n+**GIVEN** a Router instance with `sessionEnabled: false` (default)\n+**WHEN** HTTP requests are received\n+**THEN** the router SHOULD NOT track sessions\n+**AND** no session cookies SHOULD be set\n+\n+---\n+\n+## Requirement: Session ID Generation\n+\n+### Scenario: Router generates unique session ID for new session\n+\n **GIVEN** a Router with session management enabled\n **WHEN** a new client connects without a session ID\n **THEN** the router SHOULD generate a unique session ID\n-**AND** store session state for the client\n+**AND** the session ID SHOULD be a valid UUID v4 format\n \n+### Scenario: Router generates unique session IDs without collision\n+\n+**GIVEN** a Router with session management enabled\n+**WHEN** 1000 new clients connect simultaneously without session IDs\n+**THEN** the router SHOULD generate 1000 unique session IDs\n+**AND** no two sessions SHOULD share the same ID\n+\n+---\n+\n+## Requirement: Session Storage\n+\n+### Scenario: Router stores session data\n+\n+**GIVEN** a Router with session management enabled\n+**WHEN** a new session is created with session ID \"uuid-123\"\n+**THEN** the session SHOULD store: ID, backend reference, start time, last activity time, metadata\n+**AND** the session SHOULD be retrievable by session ID\n+\n ### Scenario: Router retrieves existing session\n \n-**GIVEN** a Router with active sessions\n+**GIVEN** a Router with active sessions in the store\n **WHEN** a client reconnects with a valid session ID\n-**THEN** the router SHOULD restore the session state\n-**AND** route the request to the same backend\n+**THEN** the router SHOULD restore the complete session state\n+**AND** the session's last activity time SHOULD be updated\n \n+### Scenario: Router returns nil for invalid session ID\n+\n+**GIVEN** a Router with active sessions\n+**WHEN** a client connects with a non-existent session ID \"invalid-uuid\"\n+**THEN** the router SHOULD return nil (no session found)\n+**AND** the request SHOULD be treated as a new session\n+\n+### Scenario: Session store enforces max session limit\n+\n+**GIVEN** a Router with session management enabled and `sessionMaxActive: 100`\n+**AND** 100 active sessions exist in the store\n+**WHEN** a 101st new session is requested\n+**THEN** the router SHOULD reject the new session creation\n+**OR** evict an expired session to make room\n+\n ---\n \n+## Requirement: Session Middleware\n+\n+### Scenario: Session middleware extracts session from cookie\n+\n+**GIVEN** a Router with session management enabled\n+**WHEN** an HTTP request arrives with cookie `AGENTSESSIONID=valid-uuid`\n+**THEN** the middleware SHOULD extract the session ID\n+**AND** load the corresponding session from the store\n+\n+### Scenario: Session middleware extracts session from header\n+\n+**GIVEN** a Router with session management enabled\n+**WHEN** an HTTP request arrives with header `X-Session-ID: valid-uuid` and no cookie\n+**THEN** the middleware SHOULD extract the session ID from the header\n+**AND** load the corresponding session from the store\n+\n+### Scenario: Session middleware creates new session for first request\n+\n+**GIVEN** a Router with session management enabled\n+**WHEN** an HTTP request arrives without session cookie or header\n+**THEN** the middleware SHOULD create a new session\n+**AND** set response cookie `AGENTSESSIONID` with the generated session ID\n+\n+### Scenario: Session middleware updates last activity on request\n+\n+**GIVEN** an active session with last activity time T0\n+**WHEN** a request arrives with valid session ID\n+**THEN** the session's last activity time SHOULD be updated to current time T1\n+**AND** T1 SHOULD be greater than T0\n+\n+---\n+\n+## Requirement: Session Affinity (Sticky Sessions)\n+\n+### Scenario: Router routes request to session's assigned backend\n+\n+**GIVEN** a session with backend \"backend-key-1\" stored in session data\n+**WHEN** a request arrives with the session's ID\n+**THEN** the router SHOULD route the request to backend \"backend-key-1\"\n+**AND** NOT perform load balancing across backends\n+\n+### Scenario: Router creates new session with backend assignment\n+\n+**GIVEN** a Router with session management and backend pool containing backends\n+**WHEN** a new session is created for a request routed to \"backend-2\"\n+**THEN** the session SHOULD store \"backend-2\" as its assigned backend\n+**AND** future requests with this session SHOULD route to \"backend-2\"\n+\n+### Scenario: Router handles session when backend is removed\n+\n+**GIVEN** a session with backend \"removed-backend\" stored\n+**WHEN** the \"removed-backend\" is removed from the backend pool\n+**THEN** the session SHOULD be invalidated\n+**OR** the session SHOULD be reassigned to a new valid backend\n+\n+---\n+\n+## Requirement: Session Lifecycle - Expiration\n+\n+### Scenario: Session expires after timeout\n+\n+**GIVEN** a session created at time T0 with timeout 30 minutes\n+**WHEN** the current time exceeds T0 + 30 minutes\n+**THEN** the session SHOULD be marked as expired\n+**AND** subsequent requests with this session ID SHOULD be rejected\n+\n+### Scenario: Session expiration resets on activity\n+\n+**GIVEN** a session created at T0 with timeout 30 minutes\n+**WHEN** a request arrives at T0 + 25 minutes\n+**THEN** the session expiration SHOULD be extended to T0 + 25 + 30 minutes\n+**AND** the session SHOULD remain valid\n+\n+---\n+\n+## Requirement: Session Lifecycle - Cleanup\n+\n+### Scenario: Router runs periodic session cleanup\n+\n+**GIVEN** a Router with session cleanup interval set to 5 minutes\n+**WHEN** the cleanup interval elapses\n+**THEN** expired sessions SHOULD be removed from the store\n+**AND** the active session count SHOULD decrease accordingly\n+\n+### Scenario: Cleanup removes only expired sessions\n+\n+**GIVEN** a session store with 10 active sessions and 5 expired sessions\n+**WHEN** session cleanup runs\n+**THEN** only the 5 expired sessions SHOULD be removed\n+**AND** the 10 active sessions SHOULD remain intact\n+\n+---\n+\n+## Requirement: Session Cookie Configuration\n+\n+### Scenario: Router sets secure cookie flags\n+\n+**GIVEN** a Router with `sessionCookieSecure: true` and `sessionCookieHTTPOnly: true`\n+**WHEN** a new session is created\n+**THEN** the set cookie SHOULD include `Secure` flag\n+**AND** the set cookie SHOULD include `HttpOnly` flag\n+\n+### Scenario: Router sets cookie domain\n+\n+**GIVEN** a Router with `sessionCookieDomain: \"example.com\"`\n+**WHEN** a new session is created\n+**THEN** the set cookie SHOULD include `Domain=example.com`\n+\n+### Scenario: Router sets cookie path\n+\n+**GIVEN** a Router with default configuration\n+**WHEN** a new session is created\n+**THEN** the set cookie SHOULD include `Path=/`\n+\n+---\n+\n+## Requirement: Session Metrics\n+\n+### Scenario: Router exports active session count\n+\n+**GIVEN** a Router with session management and metrics enabled\n+**WHEN** 50 active sessions exist\n+**THEN** a Prometheus gauge `router_sessions_active` SHOULD report 50\n+\n+### Scenario: Router tracks session creation rate\n+\n+**GIVEN** a Router with session management and metrics enabled\n+**WHEN** new sessions are created\n+**THEN** a Prometheus counter `router_sessions_created_total` SHOULD be incremented\n+\n+### Scenario: Router tracks session expiration rate\n+\n+**GIVEN** a Router with session management and metrics enabled\n+**WHEN** sessions expire and are cleaned up\n+**THEN** a Prometheus counter `router_sessions_expired_total` SHOULD be incremented\n+\n+### Scenario: Router exports session duration histogram\n+\n+**GIVEN** a Router with session management and metrics enabled\n+**WHEN** a session expires\n+**THEN** a Prometheus histogram `router_session_duration_seconds` SHOULD record the session lifetime\n+\n+---\n+\n+## Requirement: Graceful Shutdown\n+\n+### Scenario: Router closes session store on shutdown\n+\n+**GIVEN** a running Router with active sessions\n+**WHEN** `Shutdown()` is called\n+**THEN** the router SHOULD stop accepting new sessions\n+**AND** existing sessions SHOULD remain available until cleanup\n+\n+---\n+\n ## Acceptance Criteria\n \n-- [ ] Session IDs are generated uniquely\n-- [ ] Sessions persist across requests\n-- [ ] Sessions are cleaned up on expiration\n+- [ ] Session IDs are generated uniquely (UUID v4)\n+- [ ] Sessions persist across requests with same session ID\n+- [ ] Session cookie is set on first request when enabled\n+- [ ] Sticky sessions route to the same backend\n+- [ ] Sessions expire after configured timeout\n+- [ ] Expired sessions are cleaned up automatically\n+- [ ] Session metrics are exported (active, created, expired)\n+- [ ] Max session limit is enforced\n+- [ ] Session data includes backend, start time, last activity\n+- [ ] Cookie includes Secure and HttpOnly flags when configured\n+- [ ] Session can be extracted from cookie or X-Session-ID header\n+- [ ] Graceful shutdown completes without losing active session data\n \n ---\n \n ## References\n \n-- Delta Spec: `changes/AR-010/delta-spec.md`\n\\ No newline at end of file\n+- Delta Spec: `changes/AR-010/delta-spec.md`\n+- Proposal: `proposal.md`\n\\ No newline at end of file\n","filediff":{"file":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-010/delta-spec.md","before":"# Delta Spec: AR-010 — Router 会话管理\n\n## Overview\n\nThis delta-spec defines acceptance scenarios for implementing session management in `pkg/router`.\n\n## Base Specifications\n\n- **AR**: AR-010\n- **Module**: `pkg/router`\n- **Language**: Go\n- **Size**: M\n\n---\n\n## Background\n\nThe router module requires session management to maintain stateful connections and track client sessions to backend services.\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: Session Storage\n\n### Scenario: Router creates session for new client\n\n**GIVEN** a Router with session management enabled\n**WHEN** a new client connects without a session ID\n**THEN** the router SHOULD generate a unique session ID\n**AND** store session state for the client\n\n### Scenario: Router retrieves existing session\n\n**GIVEN** a Router with active sessions\n**WHEN** a client reconnects with a valid session ID\n**THEN** the router SHOULD restore the session state\n**AND** route the request to the same backend\n\n---\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] Session IDs are generated uniquely\n- [ ] Sessions persist across requests\n- [ ] Sessions are cleaned up on expiration\n\n---\n\n## References\n\n- Delta Spec: `changes/AR-010/delta-spec.md`","after":"# Delta Spec: AR-010 — Router 会话管理\n\n## Overview\n\nThis delta-spec defines acceptance scenarios for implementing session management in `pkg/router`.\n\n## Base Specifications\n\n- **AR**: AR-010\n- **Module**: `pkg/router`\n- **Language**: Go\n- **Size**: M\n\n---\n\n## Background\n\nThe router module requires session management to maintain stateful connections and track client sessions to backend services. This enables sticky sessions, session affinity, lifecycle management, and operational visibility into active sessions.\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: Session Configuration\n\n### Scenario: Router creates session store with default configuration\n\n**GIVEN** a Router instance is created with `sessionEnabled: true` and no explicit session configuration\n**WHEN** the router initializes\n**THEN** it SHOULD use default values: session timeout `30m`, cookie name `\"AGENTSESSIONID\"`, max active sessions `10000`, cleanup interval `5m`\n\n### Scenario: Router creates session store with custom configuration\n\n**GIVEN** a Router instance is created with session configuration: `sessionTimeout: \"60m\"`, `sessionCookieName: \"SID\"`, `sessionMaxActive: 5000`\n**WHEN** the router initializes\n**THEN** it SHOULD configure session timeout to 60 minutes, cookie name to \"SID\", and limit to 5000 concurrent sessions\n\n### Scenario: Router disables session management\n\n**GIVEN** a Router instance with `sessionEnabled: false` (default)\n**WHEN** HTTP requests are received\n**THEN** the router SHOULD NOT track sessions\n**AND** no session cookies SHOULD be set\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: Session ID Generation\n\n### Scenario: Router generates unique session ID for new session\n\n**GIVEN** a Router with session management enabled\n**WHEN** a new client connects without a session ID\n**THEN** the router SHOULD generate a unique session ID\n**AND** the session ID SHOULD be a valid UUID v4 format\n\n### Scenario: Router generates unique session IDs without collision\n\n**GIVEN** a Router with session management enabled\n**WHEN** 1000 new clients connect simultaneously without session IDs\n**THEN** the router SHOULD generate 1000 unique session IDs\n**AND** no two sessions SHOULD share the same ID\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: Session Storage\n\n### Scenario: Router stores session data\n\n**GIVEN** a Router with session management enabled\n**WHEN** a new session is created with session ID \"uuid-123\"\n**THEN** the session SHOULD store: ID, backend reference, start time, last activity time, metadata\n**AND** the session SHOULD be retrievable by session ID\n\n### Scenario: Router retrieves existing session\n\n**GIVEN** a Router with active sessions in the store\n**WHEN** a client reconnects with a valid session ID\n**THEN** the router SHOULD restore the complete session state\n**AND** the session's last activity time SHOULD be updated\n\n### Scenario: Router returns nil for invalid session ID\n\n**GIVEN** a Router with active sessions\n**WHEN** a client connects with a non-existent session ID \"invalid-uuid\"\n**THEN** the router SHOULD return nil (no session found)\n**AND** the request SHOULD be treated as a new session\n\n### Scenario: Session store enforces max session limit\n\n**GIVEN** a Router with session management enabled and `sessionMaxActive: 100`\n**AND** 100 active sessions exist in the store\n**WHEN** a 101st new session is requested\n**THEN** the router SHOULD reject the new session creation\n**OR** evict an expired session to make room\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: Session Middleware\n\n### Scenario: Session middleware extracts session from cookie\n\n**GIVEN** a Router with session management enabled\n**WHEN** an HTTP request arrives with cookie `AGENTSESSIONID=valid-uuid`\n**THEN** the middleware SHOULD extract the session ID\n**AND** load the corresponding session from the store\n\n### Scenario: Session middleware extracts session from header\n\n**GIVEN** a Router with session management enabled\n**WHEN** an HTTP request arrives with header `X-Session-ID: valid-uuid` and no cookie\n**THEN** the middleware SHOULD extract the session ID from the header\n**AND** load the corresponding session from the store\n\n### Scenario: Session middleware creates new session for first request\n\n**GIVEN** a Router with session management enabled\n**WHEN** an HTTP request arrives without session cookie or header\n**THEN** the middleware SHOULD create a new session\n**AND** set response cookie `AGENTSESSIONID` with the generated session ID\n\n### Scenario: Session middleware updates last activity on request\n\n**GIVEN** an active session with last activity time T0\n**WHEN** a request arrives with valid session ID\n**THEN** the session's last activity time SHOULD be updated to current time T1\n**AND** T1 SHOULD be greater than T0\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: Session Affinity (Sticky Sessions)\n\n### Scenario: Router routes request to session's assigned backend\n\n**GIVEN** a session with backend \"backend-key-1\" stored in session data\n**WHEN** a request arrives with the session's ID\n**THEN** the router SHOULD route the request to backend \"backend-key-1\"\n**AND** NOT perform load balancing across backends\n\n### Scenario: Router creates new session with backend assignment\n\n**GIVEN** a Router with session management and backend pool containing backends\n**WHEN** a new session is created for a request routed to \"backend-2\"\n**THEN** the session SHOULD store \"backend-2\" as its assigned backend\n**AND** future requests with this session SHOULD route to \"backend-2\"\n\n### Scenario: Router handles session when backend is removed\n\n**GIVEN** a session with backend \"removed-backend\" stored\n**WHEN** the \"removed-backend\" is removed from the backend pool\n**THEN** the session SHOULD be invalidated\n**OR** the session SHOULD be reassigned to a new valid backend\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: Session Lifecycle - Expiration\n\n### Scenario: Session expires after timeout\n\n**GIVEN** a session created at time T0 with timeout 30 minutes\n**WHEN** the current time exceeds T0 + 30 minutes\n**THEN** the session SHOULD be marked as expired\n**AND** subsequent requests with this session ID SHOULD be rejected\n\n### Scenario: Session expiration resets on activity\n\n**GIVEN** a session created at T0 with timeout 30 minutes\n**WHEN** a request arrives at T0 + 25 minutes\n**THEN** the session expiration SHOULD be extended to T0 + 25 + 30 minutes\n**AND** the session SHOULD remain valid\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: Session Lifecycle - Cleanup\n\n### Scenario: Router runs periodic session cleanup\n\n**GIVEN** a Router with session cleanup interval set to 5 minutes\n**WHEN** the cleanup interval elapses\n**THEN** expired sessions SHOULD be removed from the store\n**AND** the active session count SHOULD decrease accordingly\n\n### Scenario: Cleanup removes only expired sessions\n\n**GIVEN** a session store with 10 active sessions and 5 expired sessions\n**WHEN** session cleanup runs\n**THEN** only the 5 expired sessions SHOULD be removed\n**AND** the 10 active sessions SHOULD remain intact\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: Session Cookie Configuration\n\n### Scenario: Router sets secure cookie flags\n\n**GIVEN** a Router with `sessionCookieSecure: true` and `sessionCookieHTTPOnly: true`\n**WHEN** a new session is created\n**THEN** the set cookie SHOULD include `Secure` flag\n**AND** the set cookie SHOULD include `HttpOnly` flag\n\n### Scenario: Router sets cookie domain\n\n**GIVEN** a Router with `sessionCookieDomain: \"example.com\"`\n**WHEN** a new session is created\n**THEN** the set cookie SHOULD include `Domain=example.com`\n\n### Scenario: Router sets cookie path\n\n**GIVEN** a Router with default configuration\n**WHEN** a new session is created\n**THEN** the set cookie SHOULD include `Path=/`\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: Session Metrics\n\n### Scenario: Router exports active session count\n\n**GIVEN** a Router with session management and metrics enabled\n**WHEN** 50 active sessions exist\n**THEN** a Prometheus gauge `router_sessions_active` SHOULD report 50\n\n### Scenario: Router tracks session creation rate\n\n**GIVEN** a Router with session management and metrics enabled\n**WHEN** new sessions are created\n**THEN** a Prometheus counter `router_sessions_created_total` SHOULD be incremented\n\n### Scenario: Router tracks session expiration rate\n\n**GIVEN** a Router with session management and metrics enabled\n**WHEN** sessions expire and are cleaned up\n**THEN** a Prometheus counter `router_sessions_expired_total` SHOULD be incremented\n\n### Scenario: Router exports session duration histogram\n\n**GIVEN** a Router with session management and metrics enabled\n**WHEN** a session expires\n**THEN** a Prometheus histogram `router_session_duration_seconds` SHOULD record the session lifetime\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: Graceful Shutdown\n\n### Scenario: Router closes session store on shutdown\n\n**GIVEN** a running Router with active sessions\n**WHEN** `Shutdown()` is called\n**THEN** the router SHOULD stop accepting new sessions\n**AND** existing sessions SHOULD remain available until cleanup\n\n---\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] Session IDs are generated uniquely (UUID v4)\n- [ ] Sessions persist across requests with same session ID\n- [ ] Session cookie is set on first request when enabled\n- [ ] Sticky sessions route to the same backend\n- [ ] Sessions expire after configured timeout\n- [ ] Expired sessions are cleaned up automatically\n- [ ] Session metrics are exported (active, created, expired)\n- [ ] Max session limit is enforced\n- [ ] Session data includes backend, start time, last activity\n- [ ] Cookie includes Secure and HttpOnly flags when configured\n- [ ] Session can be extracted from cookie or X-Session-ID header\n- [ ] Graceful shutdown completes without losing active session data\n\n---\n\n## References\n\n- Delta Spec: `changes/AR-010/delta-spec.md`\n- Proposal: `proposal.md`","additions":232,"deletions":11},"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-010/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775848382295,"end":1775848382324}}}}
